
"Bret, how about we name him Jarrent Allen Reynard," she asked me with puppy eyes.
"But I thought you wanted to name him Allen."
"Oh. Well, I know how much you admired your great-grandfather," she said while placing her hand on my shoulder, "Plus I get my end of the bargain, I get to call out his middle name whenever he gets in trouble.
"Now, what makes you say that he'll be a troublemaker?"
"Well, I don't know. Maybe that smile creeping up on your face," she said bubbly.
"Bret, I know that Jarrent will be a great hero," Doctor Tyler said.
"Oh, I hope so."
"No, Bret," Doctor Tyler looked up after finished writing Jarrent's birth certificate, "I know so."